phenomenon_description: trees with translucent bark - fingers passed through
crater where trees had been - orange focal dot
feet immobilized at crater edge - could not look away
walked to crater and jumped
plant with translucent form - impulse to hide
specimens in labeled boxes vanished
survey markers vanished while placing them
ground moved only when unobserved
notes: heard sucking sounds when looking away

phenomenon_description: ground remained stable during instrument-free walk
58m transition zone - firmness 8.2 to 2.1
72m transition zone - expanded from dawn
64m zone with irregular firmness pockets
measurements impossible - compass spinning
three observers recorded different terrain
orange-red dot emerged in vision - feet stuck
two horizons simultaneously visible - compass dual reading
could not distinguish which of five was Yeller
five simultaneous paths - could not map single trajectory
observed four return to one - interval approx 8 minutes
asked to walk with Yeller - entered shack
feet sank deeper in certain sectors - ground felt attentive
ground refirmed overnight - markers returned to surface
boundary expanded 0.15m sunrise-midday contracted 0.20m sunset-midnight
lost sense of direction - could not determine which way was town
Gray Spire leaning opposite direction from previous expedition
felt dens inviting rather than resisting - pull toward center
encountered site with five simultaneous presences
Yeller spoke his full name - all five simultaneously
investigated overnight reversal - no explanation found
eight meters of channel filled overnight - four engineers collapsed
